A system built on the monad architecture from `system-system--system`.

## Structure

```
sys.toml                 System identity, versions, vocabulary (single source of truth)
manifest.toml            The system instantiated at sigma=0 (piece/v2 schema)
atom-registry.yaml       Computed atom index across all documents

bin/                     CLI tools for system observation and mutation
registry/
  data/                  Entity, relationship, event, and metric JSON records
  schemas/               JSON Schema definitions for all registry types
scales/
  -1/                    Sub-system decomposition (sigma-1)
  +1/                    Meta-level: this system as a piece within a larger system
archive/                 Historical material
coverage/                Generated reports
```

## Monad Architecture

This project was scaffolded by the system-system--system emitter. It inherits:

1. **Law 1 (System Existence)** -- `H(S) < sum H(e_i)` iff S is a system.
   The whole has less entropy than the sum of its parts. The deficit IS the structure.

2. **Law 2 (Well-Founded Composition)** -- Every system object admits a unique
   ordered tree via `(sigma, contains, precedes)`.

3. **Law 3 (Primitive Stratification)** -- 7 layers, strict nesting,
   cone of contingency.

4. **Law 4 (Scale Invariance)** -- Same schema at every sigma.
   The manifest is a fixed point.

